FBIS4-21898 "jptot015__l94063" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 3 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA EGYPT Journalist Killed by `Long-Distance' Bullet in Qalyub Journalist Killed by `Long-Distance' Bullet in Qalyub Shot in Cafe NC0304174494 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1720 GMT 3 Apr 94 NC0304174494 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 3 Apr (MENA)--Ibrahim al-Baradi'i, an AKHBAR AL- YAWM correspondent in Qalyub, was killed today after having been hit by a stray bullet. A responsible security source said that the reporter was sitting with three friends in a cafe in Qalyub, 20 km north of Cairo. As the four people left the cafe the reporter felt a pain in his neck and was bleeding. He was taken to Qalyub General Hospital where he died. A bullet was found lodged in his neck. The security source said that the victim's three friends affirmed that they did not hear any sound of gunfire, so it is likely that the stray bullet was fired from a long distance. The security agencies are continuing their investigations to determine the details of the incident.
